                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1260">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Ward, Angus I.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-24">November 24,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received November 24—4:46 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2075. ReContel 2064, November 23. Ward, by phone today, confirmed return himself
                    and others to consular compound about 2100 hours, November 21. Reported Kristan,
                    who had stood in danger gangrene, had slight relapse but again better; Tatsumi
                    improving.</p>
                <p>Poor phone contact but began preliminary work clarification missing messages.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2075; repeated Shanghai 1213, Nanking 1174, Tientsin by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
